    <!-- Getting Started -->
    <string-array name="strings_learn_getting_started_toptext">
        <item>Pinyin sounds are composed of an "initial" and a "final." Most finals are full pinyin sounds in themselves such as the most basic final, "a." The "a" final is pronounced like the "a" in the English word "father."</item>
        <item>The "b," "p," "m," and "f" initials are pronounced like their English counterparts.</item>
    </string-array>
    
    <string-array name="strings_learn_getting_started_bottomtext">
        <item>Tap the pinyin to hear how it is pronounced.</item>
        <item>Note that some initial-final combinations do not exist in Mandarin.</item>
    </string-array>

